To determine the number of atoms in 5-methyl-N-propan-2-ylpyrazin-2-amine, we must first analyze the chemical formula of the compound. 

The molecular formula of 5-methyl-N-propan-2-ylpyrazin-2-amine is C11H21N3. This indicates that there are 11 carbon (C) atoms, 21 hydrogen (H) atoms, and 3 nitrogen (N) atoms in the compound.

Therefore, the total number of atoms in 5-methyl-N-propan-2-ylpyrazin-2-amine is 11 (C) + 21 (H) + 3 (N) = 35 atoms.
